<%- include('partials/header') %>

<section class="landing-hero">
  <h1>A meal planner that respects your pantry, your budget, and your time.</h1>
  <p class="landing-tagline">
    Build a weekly plan from your own recipe library. Auto-generate the shopping list.
    Track nutrition derived from USDA. Clip recipes from NYT Cooking with one click.
  </p>

  <div class="landing-cta">
    <a class="btn primary big" href="/login">Sign in</a>
    <span class="muted small">Sign-up is by invite only — ask the owner for a code.</span>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="landing-features">
  <div class="landing-feature">
    <h3>Plan a week in a click</h3>
    <p>The planner picks recipes from your library that fit your budget, prep-time
    cap, and per-person dietary constraints. Lock favorites, regen the rest.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="landing-feature">
    <h3>Real nutrition, not estimates</h3>
    <p>Every ingredient is matched against USDA's FoodData Central. Calories,
    protein, carbs, fat, fiber, sugar, sodium — derived from what you'll actually
    cook, updating as you edit.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="landing-feature">
    <h3>Import from anywhere</h3>
    <p>Clip from NYT Cooking via the browser extension. Type recipes by hand.
    They all live alongside each other in your library.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="landing-feature">
    <h3>Households, not just users</h3>
    <p>Each member can have their own allergies, dietary constraints, and per-meal
    behavior (planned, school-provided, skipped). The planner aggregates across
    whoever's actually eating each meal.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
